    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - REMOVE - AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY
        (FIGURE 30)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302130">FIGURE 30</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1302130" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302130" filename="../figg13/G1302130.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 30. Auxiliary Drive Gear Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring from the mainshaft rear groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302131">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302131" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302131" filename="../figg13/G1302131.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. Remove Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut the lockwire and remove the bolts from the bearing retainer ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302132">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302132" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302132" filename="../figg13/G1302132.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Bearing Retainer Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert three puller screws in the specially tapped holes of retainer ring. Tighten screws
                evenly to pull the auxiliary drive gear assembly from the case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302133">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302133" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302133" filename="../figg13/G1302133.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Pull Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
